Motorized moving timelapse camera dolly with Arduino.

Parts
- Arduino nano
- Stepping motor driver board
- 4pcs LM16UU 16mm Linear Ball Bearing Bush Bushing
- 2 pcs 16mm steel pipes (trail for camera)
- Timing Belt + Timing Pulley
- 2pcs End switches
- 2x16 LCD Module Display
- 4pcs Push Button Switch
- Nema 17 step motor


|-----||                   --------                      ||
|Step ||End                |Camera|                   End||
|motor||-------belt&rail---|      |-----belt&rail--------||
|-----||switch             |      |                switch||
      ||                   --------                      ||
      |   <--------     Camera is moving       --------->
      |
 ---------   
 |Control|
 | Board |
 ---------
     |
 ---------   
 |Battery|
 |       |
 ---------


Menu
- Start/Stop 
- Setup
    - Set distance 
    - Set direction 
    - Camera FPM
        - Camera FPM (Frames per minute)
    - Time (minute)
        - Setup-Moving-time
    - Time (hour)
        - Setup-Moving-time
    - ProjectionFPS
        - FPS (Frames per second)
    - Calibrate 
    - Exit
- Go Home 
- SaveToEEPROM 
- Exit
